Package: NBA.by.Year
Title: Three Functions for NBA Data by Specified Year
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Adrian",
           family = "Varallyay",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "av2734.@columbia.cedu")
Description: This package provides three functions to use with the internally included access to NBA player data from 1950 to 2017. The first function is year_rndm_age(); it returns the age of a random player of the NBA according to specified year. The second function is oldest_by_year(); it returns the age of the oldest (one of the oldest if mulriple exist) player  of the NBA according to specified year. the third function is cor_matrx_by_year(); it returns a correlation matrix of the numerical NBA stats from a specified year.   
